header.gameNote: WNBA FINALS 2017 PRESENTED BY VERIZON - GAME 3

videos.description: Nneka Ogwumike scores the Sparks' first six points in Game 3 after shooting 7-for-22 in Games 1 and 2 of the WNBA Finals.

tracking.trackingName: WNBA_One-Play (Ogwumike starts hot after struggling in first two games) 2017/09/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Ogwumike starts hot after struggling in first two games

videos.description: Minnesota cuts into the deficit before half with a 9-0 run, highlighted by threes from Renee Montgomery and Alexis Jones.

tracking.trackingName: WNBA_One-Play (Lynx trim deficit with 9-0 run) 2017/09/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Lynx trim deficit with 9-0 run

videos.description: In the third quarter of Game 3, Chelsea Gray looks off the defense and finds Nneka Ogwumike for the finish.

tracking.trackingName: WNBA_One-Play (Gray drops no-look dime to Ogwumike) 2017/09/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Gray drops no-look dime to Ogwumike

videos.description: Candace Parker denies Alexis Jones on a layup in the fourth quarter of Game 3, as the Sparks look to hold on to a tight lead.

tracking.trackingName: WNBA_One-Play (Parker makes big-time block in Game 3) 2017/09/29 ESHEET

videos.headline: Parker makes big-time block in Game 3

videos.description: After filling the stat sheet for Los Angeles in Game 3, Candace Parker joins SC with her daughter, Lailaa, to talk about the Sparks' win over the Lynx in the WNBA Finals.

tracking.trackingName: COM_WNBA Interview (Parker credits defense for Sparks' Game 3 win) 2017/09/29 SC

videos.headline: Parker credits defense for Sparks' Game 3 win

videos.description: Candace Parker dominates on both sides of the floor and Nneka Ogwumike records a double-double in Los Angeles' 75-64 win over Minnesota, giving the Sparks a 2-1 lead in the WNBA Finals.
videos.headline: Sparks a win away from repeating
